HEADWORD: Scatter-brain
<hw>Scat"ter-brain`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A giddy or
thoughtless person; one incapable of concentration or attention.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>scatter-brains</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

